RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHANGHAI POINT rated on the front end toward the outside on the backstretch, moved clear when allowed three wide on the bend, widened command and angled in upper stretch, weaved out and back in inside the last eighth but maintained full control under steady handling. BACKSHOT prominent between horses, was steadied from the half mile marker to the seven-sixteenths pole behind traffic, got through three wide leaving the turn and pulled clear for second the final furlong. TAPIT SAM helped prompt the pace from outside, lost ground four wide through the bend, lacked the needed late bid but edged ahead for third late. STUMP vied for the lead between rivals, did not stay with SHANGHAI POINT while two wide on the turn and slowly wore down for the drive. ONE WAY HOME also contested the pace between horses on the backstretch but began to fade along the rail before finishing a half mile. IT'S BELLAMY TIME hustled vigorously from inside, gave way along the rail before the end of three furlongs.

MUD ISLAND raced closest to the early speed, threatened two wide on the bend, floated out some into the stretch and began to fade. R H SMOAKEM never far off the inside, failed to menace. RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAHOKIA POSSE advanced in tight quarters to vie for the lead between rivals on the backstretch, was two wide on the bend, gained the rail upper stretch, took the lead inside the last eighth, was clear of the rest with a sixteenth left and held WICKED SKY at bay under steady handling. WICKED SKY forwardly placed toward the outside, progressed four wide on the turn and rallied belatedly in the lane. FERGIE ATTACK vied for the early lead outside rivals, moved ahead of the rest three wide on the bend but began to slowly wear down inside the final furlong. HER SPEAKER'S ON somewhat awkward at the break, advanced between horses, angled out through the turn, came five wide into the stretch, also found best stride too late but was clearly best of the rest. SILVER EYES contested the pace from inside on the backstretch, did not keep up into the bend, gradually angled out, was four wide in the lane then ran evenly the rest of the way. DON'T TELL ALYCE soon trailed, saved ground, passed tired ones upper stretch, altered out for a clear path inside the final sixteenth and improved position without threatening. FEATURED POWER chased from outside, faded four wide on the turn, swung out further for the drive and also passed some tired ones late. SKIP TO BALI displayed early speed between foes, gained the rail midway on the bend and began to fade before finishing a half mile. MOLLY'S TEMPLE was a contender between horses on the backstretch but gave way three wide on the turn. HOT N FRESH showed little in a wide trip.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JAMAICAN TRAFFIC stalked the early speed from outside, took the lead three wide when allowed on the bend then steadily opened up under urging in the lane to prove much the best. CARICIA prominent between rivals, went for the lead two wide on the turn, was no match for JAMAICAN TRAFFIC when set down for the drive, began to wear down deep stretch but lasted for the place. HIGHTAILING IT lugged in some leaving the chute, bumped SLEEPY CAT, was altered to the outside, threatened four wide on the bend but leveled off in the lane. BLAZE BEAUTY void of early speed, was wide throughout, passed tired ones upper stretch and made up minor ground on the place and show horses inside the final eighth. TINA'S TAPIZAR in contention early just off the inside, altered in nearing the five-furlong marker trying to stay clear of CARICIA, bumped SLEEPY CAT, was steadied, retreated slightly from path three on the bend and gave way for the stretch run. SLEEPY CAT overcame being bumped leaving the chute and near the five-furlong pole to set a pressured pace but began to fade along the rail before finishing a half mile.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FROSTED ECLAIR rated on the front end from outside, moved clear from path two on the bend, floated out some entering the lane then maintained control under steady urging. CANTOO hesitated at the break, gradually angled out as she advanced on the backstretch, lost ground four then five wide through the turn, rallied in the stretch and took over second inside the last sixteenth. MOON PIES IMAGE without early speed, altered in with a half mile to go, progressed two wide on the bend, altered out six wide for a clear path upper stretch, closed well and caught BE MY BESTIE for third. BE MY BESTIE shared the lead between rivals on the backstretch, gained the rail into the turn, did not stay with FROSTED ECLAIR and gradually wore down the final furlong. GHAALEB'S CITY a step slow at the start, moved to the inside early on, progressed along the rail on the bend, came off the inside some for a clear path into the stretch, could only make up minor ground in the late going but was easily best of the others. SHINE DOWN broke slowly and failed to menace in a wide trip. MUD HUT prompted the early pace from outside, was three then four wide through the turn and gave way for the drive. RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAMARITA rated off the early speed, progressed from outside after two furlongs, took the lead from path three entering the lane, moved clear and was kept to urging until the last seventy yards. CATCHUSIFYOUCAN prominent outside PRINCESS STELLA, swung outside SAMARITA into the stretch, gained second inside the final furlong, began to level off in the waning yards but lasted for the place. RONAN well back early, picked up her pace along the rail after a quarter mile, swung out to path three entering the stretch, was crowded briefly inside the final eighth then pulled clear for third as she continued her bid the last sixteenth. DOROTA moved to the inside midway on the backstretch, had a striking position along the rail on the bend, began to flatten in the lane, altered out some for a clear path inside the furlong marker and finished evenly. PRINCESS STELLA (IRE) hesitated at the break then bore in, was corrected, rushed up from inside to gain a clear lead before finishing the first eighth, was just off the rail taking the turn and gave way inside the final three-sixteenths. RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOT TO BE DENIED soon had the lead, showed the way in hand from inside, moved clear when allowed on the second bend, came off the rail some entering the lane, was all in the late going and kept WILDCAT BOBBIE at bay. WILDCAT BOBBIE settled well off the inside, commenced her bid after a half mile, lost ground five wide through the second turn, continued her rally in the stretch, gradually lugged in as she closed on the weakening leader inside the final furlong and had to settle for second best. THINK BLUE was four wide taking the first bend, gradually angled in on the backstretch to be just outside NOT TO BE DENIED, did not stay with that one on the second turn, angled out some upper stretch and ran evenly the rest of the way. JULIAISON vied for the lead briefly between rivals, was settled back once on the backstretch, had the rail through the second turn, lodged a mild bid to gain a striking position with a furlong to go but leveled off instead. MY MORNING GAL settled well off the inside on the backstretch, made her bid four wide on the second bend but weakened for the drive. MISS WINDY SLEW prominent between horses from the beginning, was three wide taking the second turn then gave way for the stretch run.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 74. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 26000. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING 10,000 FOR HORSES THAT HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 19 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FAST CROSS TRAFFIC was away slowly, cautious to avoid the loose horse leaving the chute, altered in soon after entering the main track, roused after two furlongs, swiftly circled rivals under urging through the bend, came into the lane four wide, angled toward the inside upper stretch, steadily lengthened command and was kept to task to the wire. RUN THE TABLE forwardly placed from outside, was three wide through the turn, battled for second inside the final furlong and edged ahead for the place inside the last sixteenth. I'M YOUR CAPTAIN pressed ON THE MONEY RED from outside, drifted out badly leaving the bend but was closing in for second through the waning yards. ON THE MONEY RED was hustled along to set a pressured pace from inside, came off the rail some into the turn, was no match for FAST CROSS TRAFFIC when set down for the drive, was challenged for second nearing the final sixteenth, slowly yielded and lugged in some approaching the wire. BRIANS WAY was shuffled back from tight quarters nearing the end of the first eighth, advanced along the rail on the bend, lacked the needed late kick in the stretch and was steadied behind ON THE MONEY RED in the waning yards. DIAMND CON SUERTE was also shuffled back from tight quarters before finishing the first furlong, retreated two wide on the turn and only made up minor ground on the second flight deep stretch. TRUIST stumbled badly at the start and lost his rider. SKIP AWAY CARTER refused to start. There was a stewards' inquiry into TRUIST'S and SKIP AWAY CARTER'S start. No action was taken after their review.
